Lord Alli
Founder



                                Back 
                            


Waheed Alli is Chairman of ASOS the UK’s largest independent online fashion and beauty retailer which offers over 40,000 branded and own label product lines sold worldwide. ASOS is listed on the stock exchange with a market cap of over $2bn.
 

Waheed is also Chairman of Silvergate, founded in 2011, an international media business with offices in London and New York. The business owns or controls the intellectual property rights to brands, characters and literary estates with a strong publishing heritage such as The World of Beatrix Potter and The Octonauts and seeks to develop those assets across a range of media and merchandise formats. This includes the creation of new television productions, new publishing ranges, and associated lines of toys and merchandise.


Waheed is also a director of Olga Productions which makes Paul O’Grady’s television and he is his agent.
 

In the 1990s Waheed was Managing Director of one of the largest independent production companies in the UK.  He is also responsible, along with Charlie Parsons and Bob Geldof, for the creation of long running TV reality show Survivor.
 

He was appointed a working Labour peer in July 1998 and is now an active member of the House of Lords, Parliament UK.
 

Waheed is also a patron of The Elton John Aids Foundation, Chancellor of De Montfort University and President of the National Youth Theatre.











